Data Dictionary

Table
  
Table ------------------------------Column -------------------------- Data --------------------------------- Type  Description
properties -------------------------- id ------------------------------INT (PK) -----------------------Unique identifier for each property listing.
 -----------------------------------neighborhood_id  ------------------INT (FK) ----------------------Reference to the neighborhoods table.
 ------------------------------------list_price --------------------- DECIMAL -------------------------The initial asking price of the property.
sales-------------------------------  property_id--------------------  INT (FK) -----------------------Link to the specific property sold.
------------------------------------ sale_price----------------------  DECIMAL ------------------------The final agreed transaction price.
 ------------------------------------days_on_market ------------------- INT--------------------------- Duration from listing to sale date.
--------------------------------------agents  commission_rate  ---------FLOAT ------------------------ The percentage of the sale price earned by the agent.
neighborhoods  -----------------------school_rating  --------------------INT-------------------------- Quality score (1-10) of local education.
inspections -------------------------- severity_level ------------------ INT --------------------------Impact score of property issues (1=Low, 10=Critical).

 
